# Project Structure

This is a .NET Core API project with a layered architecture. The main components are:

## Core Components
- [ApiService](mdc:ApiService) - Main API service containing controllers and models
- [ApiService.Entity](mdc:ApiService.Entity) - Entity models and data transfer objects
- [ApiService.Interface](mdc:ApiService.Interface) - Interfaces for services
- [ApiService.Business](mdc:ApiService.Business) - Business logic layer
- [ApiService.Implement](mdc:ApiService.Implement) - Implementation of interfaces
- [ApiService.Core](mdc:ApiService.Core) - Core utilities and helpers

## Key Controllers
- [ApiService/Controllers/AuthController.cs](mdc:ApiService/Controllers/AuthController.cs) - Authentication controller with login, refresh token, and Google OAuth
- [ApiService/Controllers/UserExamAttemptController.cs](mdc:ApiService/Controllers/UserExamAttemptController.cs) - Exam attempt management and scoring

## Database
- [Db](mdc:Db) - Database scripts and migrations

